,Recommended,280220,10302123,"Posted: 31 May, 2014",all,alb,"I've played Creeper World since I first saw the flash version of it online, and have been hooked to it ever since. I saw this on Steam and I instantly knew I had to buy it. Plays just like the first Creeper World, on an overhead view of the map. If you've played Creeper World 2: Academy online, you'll have some of, if not all of what you need to know about the characters in this game. The story is pretty entertaining, I found myself wanting to play more every time I finished a mission.If you're one of those people that couldn't care less about the story of a game, and only care about the gameplay itself, it's got more that what you could ever possibly want. The amount of levels in this game are enough to last you for a loooong time. Each level is different, each one is difficult, and each one forces you to think about how you'll need to start. Sometimes you'll be cornered, sometimes surrounded, and sometimes you won't even have a lot of time to prepare. You would start off in an area with a high wall that has holes in it, and the creeper is advancing from all around you, you can only seal off a few of the holes. In some levels you won't have much time before you're overwhelmed, and in some you might need to use different strategies. This game will have surprises in store for you if you're new to it's universe and gameplay.As for the levels, I have yet to put even a small dent into the other sectors, as they contain probably hundreds of more challenging, and maybe even impossible levels. Even with the story missions, as I progressed through them I found myself taking almost an hour to beat them. This will be a time consumer. And on top of the other sectors, there is also the DMD, which is basically loaded with user created maps. So if you somehow manage to top every single level with the game, there's plenty more where that came from.If you've played Creeper World before, you will definitely love this game. It's all of the original gameplay loaded with levels, some new tools, a map creator, and, in my opinion, a story that will leave you wanting to continue and find out what happens next."
