,Recommended,280220,19302468,"Posted: 26 November, 2015",all,noirsilt,"This is 3rd in the Creeper series and it shows;headline feature from previous entries now casually sit in your tool box, and years of polish and good UI choices run through the experience.This is the Creeper series at it's very best,The core game is a pseudo tower-defense game, where the enemy ""creeper"" is modeled on thermodynamic movement (enemy propagates through the level like heat through a medium), and your personal infrastructure in modeled on packet switching.The benefit of this is a game that's a very unique variant on the genre, and visually is wholly singular.Packets zip about your network as they beat back the horrors of living entropy!Worth highlighting is the story; minimalist in a very impressive way. A few text back-and-forths at the start of a level are all you get, but they deliver fully on the feeling and weight of being trapped at the end of a dead universe; alone in the empty infinity but for your sole friend.It would be nice if production values were a little higher. Sprites could be better; and the music though good, does get repetitive with it's few songs. Though the core experience is never deeply hurt by these weak points.The game's single biggest flaw is in it's dynamics. If you survive the first few minutes of a fight it becomes a rather rote process of slowly expanding your territory, until 30-60 min later you've zapped the last enemy.There are frequent small decisions to make, but very few large ones.Despite the narrative weight of the-end-of-all-things and the cool high-energy packet switching & blasting of your little empire, the game ultimately feels like a casual experience.Mellowly click away, pruning your little bonsai death machine until you've won.A fine experience, but RTS and 4x fans will be yearning for more difficulty and substance.Though some will wish it had more challenge, ""Arc Eternal"" is still an excellent little game!(And it's probably cheep by the time you read this.)Its uniqueness makes it well worth your time and money!"
