,Recommended,280220,9698022,"Posted: 1 April, 2014",all,zivyterc,Highly recommended!
76561197966299813,Recommended,280220,9701499,"Posted: 1 April, 2014",all,Smingleigh,"A satisfying game, where the enemy is totally predictable (it is literally as dumb as thick goo), yet no less challenging for that.The eponymous ""Creeper"" is a thick sludge that spews out of emitters in the game world, and you must force it back. The creeper isn't smart, it doesn't think, and it doesn't even have anything in the way of AI. What it has instead, is a pleasingly viscous fluid simulation. It flows downhill, it pools in low areas, and it can't cross high terrain without building up behind it and overflowing it like a dam. This is the key to the game. Work out where the creeper will flow, and divert or destroy it to survive and achieve your objectives.The game is one of thoughtful management. Rarely is there urgency, except during scripted missions, or if you seriously mess up and end up watching a purple tidal wave swamp your low-lying energy collectors. That's okay! The challenge is one of incremental advancement and the satisfying conquest of areas that were drowned under a layer of creeper 8 stacks high.I'm a little concerned with balance issues (there is one early-acquired unit which seems overpowered, especially in groups) but I'm content to tend my garden of creeper without abusing it, which is an unusual state of affairs."
