76561197999356538,Recommended,280220,11491135,"Posted: 31 July, 2014",all,MattStriker,"Creeper World 3 is one of those funny little games that don't quite fit any established genre.It's broadly speaking an RTS, but it doesn't really play like any other RTS on the market. It also has some tower defense elements to it, but again, it's quite different from any ""true"" tower defense game.Like a TD, it's a game about fighting a relentless enemy that keeps coming at you along predictable paths.Like a regular RTS, you build structures to harvest resources, and your towers can move around (this isveryimportant on many levels) once they're built.Your enemy is a liquid with no ability to react to your activities. It simply spreads from emitters and flows downhill, forming pools that eventually overflow and flood the map. There's no enemy AI worth mentioning. And it's still surprisingly challenging, because there's alotof the stuff, and your resources can be quite limited. You'll have to make careful decisions about where to build something andwhenbecause running out of power at the wrong time can cause your entire line of defense to collapse in a real hurry.It's a very simple concept, with only a few types of unit, a very straightforward upgrade system and extremely barebones presentation...and it adds up to a highly addictive game with surprising depth once you get into the tougher maps.All in all, I can definitely recommend this."
