,Recommended,280220,9665694,"Posted: 29 March, 2014",all,danly,"This is a surprisingly compelling little game.The gist is that you are fighting back against goo of the sort you'd expect to find in a dystopian science fiction novel. To do so, you maintain an array of collectors interconnected by an energy grid that conveys construction and ammunition resources throughout its network. You plunk down turrets, which can later be moved, that feed off the grid. The goo itself has a few tricks that complicate matters, but I'll leave that to you to discover.What sounds simple ends up making for a fairly compelling asynchronous RTS. Wrapped in an intriguing story, and garnished with pleasing graphics, it ends up being a fun ride."
