76561198028290751,Recommended,280220,26928541,"Posted: 23 November, 2016",all,Aredict,"An awesome game for fans of defense, strategy, and single-player RTS games.  Near infinite replayability beyond the campaign levels with extra-hard levels/custom-created maps (the game has its own scripting language that diehard fans are exploring tremendously).Pros:-The liquid-based enemy of the Creeper is totally unique-Satisfying ""combat"" and a real feeling of accomplishment that is visually rewarded when overcoming an obstacle (Your energy grid and supply lines grant amazing visual feedback)-Surprisingly deep decision making for some of the harder maps, but everything is always fair - no cheap shots or surprises-Play at your own pace, pausing to build or plan ahead, and saving/loading whenever you want (You can play a mission slowly and safely and eventually overcome anything, or push yourself to the limit and try to beat them even faster or more efficiently)-Low cost for the amount of replayability offered-Highly customizable - Sound, controls, visibility/colors of elements on the game screenCons:-There's a definite learning curve beyond the main missions that may seem off-putting at first - complexity of units, resources, mechanics, terminology-Fans of defense games with direct player combat/intervention (FPS controls or special abilities) may not like the nearly fully automated weapons/enemy-The art style is a bit simplistic, even if you're a fan of pixel art-y or tiny models, and can cause the visuals to blend together for new players-Some of the sound design can get repetitive, especially when you've got large scale bases and battles"
