76561198053561874,Recommended,280220,17994370,"Posted: 12 September, 2015",all,Menzagitat,"(Before edit, play time was 150-170 hours)You get one very nice campain.The game has an integrated map editor and you can play the custom maps made by other players.There are also two areas with lots of auto-generated maps, some of them very difficult and few of them impossible.I recomend the campain for those who like tower defense and strategy games.I recomend the extremly difficult maps for those who like to discover alone how to improve and optimize.I have not played yet any of the player made maps, so I can tell little about them. I know that you can use scripts and custom images when you create the maps so possibly the comunity maps might be interesting too. You can rate those too and I seen a thriving comunity there :)Edit:(08-Oct-2015) Play time: 209 hoursI made two maps, a normal map and one with scrips.The programming language used in scrips is based on ""reverse polish notation"" concept:- you put the values into the stack and the operand afterward on top of them- the operand will combine the top elements (these are consumed)- the result is being placed back to the top of the stackThe concept is very different from normal programming languages.They say on the wiki that you do not have to be a programmer to learn this language.I say this is true for any programming language.And after you learn it, you are a programmer. Not an experienced or profesional one, but a programmer nevertheless.Regarding the maps: I made them for myself, as hard as possible. Some people do not like hard maps.I will continue occasionally to make maps inbetween other games.I avoid playing custom maps to avoid being influenced by their ideas."
