,Recommended,280220,16874761,"Posted: 4 July, 2015",all,Tzaot,"A simple yet amazingly versatile concept: Build against goo.In Creeper World 3 you take command of an automated base that gathers energy and ore and uses it to supply a diversity of weapons and utility tools, such as terraforming, to survive an seemingly endless onslaught of an oozy, purple substance called ""Creeper"".Much like the Creeper that some of you know form Starcraft, this slow flood will damage your buildings.In order to obtain, hold or destory a range of objectives, you will have to protect your base by clever build defences, until it provides enough energy to conquer and scrub-free new land. New land means new buildingspace and more energy and the circle repeats till victory.The strong side of this strategy puzzle game is, that the way you expand is totally up to you.Artillery and dropping additional bases is my recommended tactic.It is not an easy game.Players of Starcraft or similar micro/macro skill based RTS games will probably enjoy the level of APM that is needed to hunt the online highscores in this game.Apart from being a challenging and fun strategy and puzzle game, Creeper World also has an own storyline.A space captain and an ancient AI take on a seemingly hopeless battle against an alien race that teleports emitters of Creeper onto every planet which ever existed. As they try to understand the relentless hatred of their alien adversaries, the duo of lone survivors discovers a conspiracy that seems to be encoded into the very fabric of the universe itself.It tends to stretch dialogues to create tention, which works but is a bit exhausting. Also the characters are aggressively unaware of the mysteries that surround them. But perhaps that's just me."
