76561198068982092,Recommended,280220,23226275,"Posted: 26 May, 2016",all,Sgt. Buttersworth [E-308],"This might actually be my favourite RTS(ish?) game.The gameplay is only singleplayer and very much oriented around building a defense grid to resist and overcome a stream of Creeper. The Creeper is a liquid like entity that will accumulate and destroy your buildings if your defense isn't up fast enough.One of the features I think it the coolest about this game is the terrain. Heigh can vary between 1 and 10 and will didctate how the Creeper will flow on the map. It's also possible to terraform it to create things like walls or flatten the place where you want to build.But walls won't help you forever. Creeper isn't limited to the height of 10 and will accumulate untill you destroy all the spawners.That's the basic of it. There is also a few more ennemies and you have about 11 buildings to adapt to each scenario.The main story is cool. The first half will introduce you to new features and the second half will have unique levels to challenge you, especially toward the end. The whole thing is lead by a mysterious sci-fy story.And the best part is that the story is the small part of the game. After the few hours you need to complete it, you have countless more missions to play and also user-created ones.Nice defense RTS, tons of content. It might not be for everyone but check it out!"
