76561198011709181,Recommended,280220,35126647,Posted: 22 September,all,panbient,"This is a prime example of a game that requires a ""Mixed"" option for a review.  The only reason I'm choosing Positive is because I got it on a nearly 90% off sale.  This is absolutely not worth the regular price.It's more of a relaxing activity rather than any sort of challenging game.  There's no actual AI.  It's you vs. the environment that reacts the exact same in every map.  The only real 'diffuclty' is the initial setup.  Once you figure out how / where to place your initial HQ it just becomes a matter of time as resources are inifinite.Speaking of time, the leaderboards are borked.  I have yet to see a map where the time to complete is over a minute (most seem to be around 30 seconds).It's a great alternative to Free Cell / Solitaire / Minesweeper for a relaxing thing to play on your PC, but it's pretty bland as a tower defense game."
